    Several syntactic devices can be used to indicate the speech act being performed: the most obvious are explicit performative verbs such as &amp;quot;I hereby request you to ...&amp;quot;, and mood (indicative for assertions, imperative for requests to do, interrogative for requests to inform).
    But the mood of an utterance is well known to not completely specify its illocutionary force: 1.a-b can be requests to close the door, 1.c-e can be requests to t